@node "introduction" " Introduction"
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| 1. Introduction                                                            |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                            |
|  Why?                                                                      |
| That question has been asked for ages.. Why are we living?, why does the   |
| sock always disappear in the laundry?, why is PC more used than Amiga?,    |
| why has some bozo made ANOTHER wall?                                       |
|                                                                            |
|  The answers?                                                              |
| Sorry, I'm the wrong person to ask, except for the kast question. It is    |
| about that one that this manual is about.                                  |
|                                                                            |
|  The Answer!                                                               |
| During a period of about 4 months a small door asked the users when they   |
| logged out of my BBS if they wanted to leave a single-line message.        |
| Discussions soon emerged on this door, unfortunately these were impossible |
| to follow unless you logged on to the BBS several times per day! Shortly:  |
|  No one knew what was happening!                                           |
| So one day I developed the door to v2.0 by turning it into a Wall. That's  |
| why the door still is called Mezz. But to show that it was a new version   |
| I added Wall to the name.                                                  |
|  After that I 'happended' to keep developing the door to what you're       |
| reading about now!                                                         |
|                                                                            |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
              Planet 98% full. Delete all PC-users (Y/Y)?


@endnode
@node "installation" " Installation, Requirements and Configuration"
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| 2. Installation, Requirements and Configuration                            |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                            |
|  MezzWall should work on any Amiga. However Arexx is required.             |
|  Don't forget that RexxMast must be started before the door is started!    |
|                    ~~~~~~~~ ~~~~ ~~ ~~~~~~~                                |
|                                                                            |
|  Installation:                                                             |
| 1. Put the file "MezzWall" at any location. This is the program.           |
| 2. Put the files "mezz.dta" and "mezz.cfg" at any location                 |
|                                                                            |
| 3. Edit your BBS's datafiles and install it. Please rember that MezzWall   |
|    must be started with RX and need the following arguments (in this       |
|    order)                                                                  |
| The user's screenwidth                                                     |
| The user's screenheight                                                    |
| The user's status                                                          |
| Path and name of the configurationfile                                     |
| The user's name                                                            |
|                                                                            |
| 4. Load the file "mezz.cfg" into a texteditor and edit it (instructions    |
|    in it)                                                                  |
|                                                                            |
| 5. If you want to personalize your wall then edit the languagefile you're  |
|    using (e.g "EngMezz.dta")                                               |
|                                                                            |
|                                                                            |
|  Installation in NT-Pro BBS:es:                                            |
| 1. Put the file "MezzWall.nt" to any location. This is the program         |
| 2. Put the files "mezz.dta" and "mezz.cfg" to any location                 |
| 3. If you want the wall to be accessible from within the BBS, add the      |
|    following lines to "NT:S/Command.dat":                                  |
|    NAME=Klotter                                                            |
|    TYPE=Rx NT:Rexx/MezzWall.nt %x %y %s %n Doors:Mezz.cfg "%u"             |
|    FLAGS=Interactive                                                       |
|    VILKA=klottrar pĺ MezzWall                                              |
| 4. If you want the wall to be started when someone is loggin in or out;    |
|   add this line to "NT:Txtfiles/Bulletin.txt" or "NT:Txtfiles/Goodbye.txt" |
|    %i<Rx NT:Rexx/MezzWall.nt %x %y %s %n Doors:Mezz.cfg %u                 |
| 5. The paths and arguments can and SHOULD BE CHANGED! Keep on reading to   |
|    find out how!                                                           |
|                                                                            |
|  The following arguments are needed. They have to be in this specified     |
|  order:                                                                    |
| The user's screenwidth                                                     |
| The user's screenheight                                                    |
| The user's status                                                          |
| The user's nodenummer                                                      |
| Path and name of the configurationfile                                     |
| The user's name                                                            |
|                                                                            |
| 6. Load the file "mezz.cfg" into a texteditor and edit it (instructions    |
|    in it)                                                                  |
|                                                                            |
| 7. If you want to personalize your wall then edit the languagefile you're  |
|    using (e.g "EngMezz.dta")                                               |
|                                                                            |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
              Intel Inside - Idiot Outside


@endnode
@node "usage" " Usage"
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| 3. Usage                                                                   |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                            |
|  When the program is run, the number of lines you've chosen is showed.     |
| By only using one line, the Wall can be turned into a LastMezz.            |
|                                                                            |
|  If the user choose the character defined as "Yes" in the CFG-file he/she  |
| will be asked to type in the message. Any other answer is assumed to be    |
| a "No".                                                                    |
|                                                                            |
|  If an "e" is typed instead of a Yes or No and the user have a status      |
| above the one stated in the CFG-file he/she comes to the online-edit mode. |
|                                                                            |
|  The message the user types may not be longer than 72 characters. If it is |
| it will be truncated to 72 characters.                                     |
|                                                                            |
|  If the message is shorter than the number you've specified in the CFG-    |
| file it is replaced with a the message from the languagefile or nothing if |
| tha string in the languagefile is "NADA".                                  |
|                                                                            |
|  If the user types in the character defined in the CFG-file for down-      |
| loading he/she gets the text in ASCII-format downloaded (NT-Pro version    |
| only!).                                                                    |
|                                                                            |
|  If the text contains one of the words in the configurationfile at seven   |
| and downwards it is replaced with another message or nothing depending on  |
| what you've specified in the CFG-file.                                     |
|                                                                            |
|  After that, the user gets to choose between 7 ANSI-colours. If the user   |
| selects anything but the numbers 1-7 here a the message gets a random      |
| colour.                                                                    |
|                                                                            |
|  Now the user gets to choose if he/she wants the line centered (in the     |
| middle). It is done automatically if the user choose anything but the      |
| character defined as "No" in the CFG-file!                                 |
|                                                                            |
|  If the logfile-alternative is on (1 in the CFG-file) the text, date, time |
| and the user's name is saved in the logfile.                               |
|                                                                            |
|  You can easily change in the data or logfile since they're both in ASCII  |
| format.                                                                    |
|                                                                            |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
                Win95 isn't a virus - Viruses does something!


@endnode
@node "features" " Features"
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| 4. Features                                                                |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                            |
| * Can be run in ANY language since it uses a languagefile!                 |
| * Can be used both as Wall and Lastmezz since the SysOp can adjust the     |
|   number of lines to be shown                                              |
| * Selectable censoring of for example BBS-adverts!                         |
| * Online-editing for users who have a special status                       |
| * Full ANSI-support                                                        |
| * All data is saved in ASCII-format which makes it easy for you to change! |
| * Easy to configure                                                        |
| * Can give random colours to the lines                                     |
| * Selectable centring of the text                                          |
| * All lines can be forced to be of a minimun length                        |
| * Can save important information in a logfile                              |
| * Saves time and date in the logfile                                       |
| * Uses a configurationfile for easier use                                  |
| * The whole look can be changed except the titleline!                      |
| * Automatically adjusts after the users screenwidth                        |
| * Automatically adjusts after the users screenheight                       |
| * The wall can be downloaded                                               |
| * Freeware                                                                 |
| * Good manual(?)                                                           |
|                                                                            |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
 Win95 IS the OS of the future - It only works on the computers of the future


@endnode
